    "rationale": "The fscanf ABI entrypoint reads FrankenLibC-managed streams through the native libio registry and parses with scanf_core. The __isoc99_wscanf entrypoint is a C99 alias into FrankenLibC's native wide scanf path, which narrows the wide format and delegates writes to the shared native scanf value writer. The remaining census symbols are libio registry/bootstrap, raw fd reads, alias reachability, and errno propagation, not host libc scanf semantic delegation."
